1
00:00:00,104 --> 00:00:04,956
NO TAIL TO TELL

2
00:00:04,980 --> 00:00:07,286
CHARACTERS, LOCATIONS, INCIDENTS,

3
00:00:07,310 --> 00:00:09,977
AND GROUPS IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS.

4
00:00:11,133 --> 00:00:12,218
{\an8}What if…

5
00:00:15,471 --> 00:00:17,139
{\an8}I don't want to be normal?

6
00:00:19,016 --> 00:00:19,892
{\an8}What?

7
00:00:19,975 --> 00:00:22,436
{\an8}If you're just going to erase my memory

8
00:00:23,354 --> 00:00:25,773
{\an8}and be the only one
who remembers this moment,

9
00:00:26,815 --> 00:00:29,568
{\an8}then I should be allowed to do
at least this much, right?

10
00:00:30,819 --> 00:00:32,154
{\an8}What do you mean…

11
00:00:47,545 --> 00:00:49,797
{\an8}What…
…do you think you're doing?

12
00:00:50,422 --> 00:00:52,675
{\an8}Unlike you, I'm not good
at doing things half-heartedly.

13
00:00:52,758 --> 00:00:55,928
If I decide to do something,
I have to put all my heart into it.

14
00:00:56,011 --> 00:00:59,056
Wait. What do you mean?

15
00:01:00,015 --> 00:01:02,268
Let's date. For real.

16
00:01:03,477 --> 00:01:04,603
I'm serious.

17
00:01:08,524 --> 00:01:11,777
You're still wet behind the ears.
Where did you learn to do that?

18
00:01:12,444 --> 00:01:14,405
What do you think you're doing?

19
00:01:15,364 --> 00:01:17,449
Why are you so flustered?

20
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:20,286
- Is there a problem?
- Of course there is.

21
00:01:20,369 --> 00:01:23,956
Once we go back to how we were,
we'll never see each other again.

22
00:01:24,039 --> 00:01:26,083
So you coming on so strong like this

23
00:01:27,209 --> 00:01:29,253
is overwhelming.

24
00:01:29,795 --> 00:01:32,006
Then you shouldn't have led me on.

25
00:01:32,089 --> 00:01:33,465
I'm just getting started.

26
00:01:35,217 --> 00:01:37,344
Why? Do you want to stop?

27
00:01:40,556 --> 00:01:42,391
When did I ever lead you on?

28
00:01:45,352 --> 00:01:49,148
Don't think about running,
and don't just dip your toes in.

29
00:01:54,903 --> 00:01:56,989
Let's do this right. You and I both.

30
00:01:59,617 --> 00:02:01,535
From now on, I'm done joking around.

31
00:02:14,381 --> 00:02:16,425
EPISODE 9
LOVE ATTACK

32
00:02:18,218 --> 00:02:19,219
That nine-tailed fox.

33
00:02:20,387 --> 00:02:22,389
She said she became human.

34
00:02:23,223 --> 00:02:24,725
What?

35
00:02:25,809 --> 00:02:29,063
She's just an ordinary human now.

36
00:02:30,773 --> 00:02:32,191
An ordinary human?

37
00:02:34,943 --> 00:02:36,487
An ordinary human.

38
00:02:39,698 --> 00:02:42,159
Then that fox

39
00:02:43,243 --> 00:02:44,995
has no power anymore,

40
00:02:45,829 --> 00:02:47,998
and there's no reason to be afraid of her.

41
00:02:52,544 --> 00:02:54,421
This just got interesting.

42
00:02:55,839 --> 00:02:57,591
What are you going to do?

43
00:02:57,675 --> 00:02:59,635
- About what?
- What do you think?

44
00:03:00,469 --> 00:03:03,472
Now that things are in our favor,
you're not going after that damn fox?

45
00:03:03,555 --> 00:03:04,473
Why should I?

46
00:03:05,766 --> 00:03:07,101
What?

47
00:03:07,184 --> 00:03:09,019
Whether I skin it or roast it,

48
00:03:09,103 --> 00:03:12,272
I won't get blood on my hands
unless there's something to gain.

49
00:03:13,565 --> 00:03:16,068
Wait, what does that…

50
00:03:17,403 --> 00:03:20,197
They say cultivated beasts have an orb.

51
00:03:20,823 --> 00:03:23,701
Dragons hold dragon orbs
to call the wind and rain.

52
00:03:23,784 --> 00:03:27,955
Nine-tailed foxes have fox beads
to perform their infinite tricks.

53
00:03:29,248 --> 00:03:32,084
But if that fox
really became an ordinary human,

54
00:03:32,710 --> 00:03:35,129
her bead must've already shattered
and vanished.

55
00:03:35,963 --> 00:03:38,173
So, I'm not interested anymore.

56
00:03:38,799 --> 00:03:41,135
But look at what we suffered

57
00:03:41,218 --> 00:03:43,554
because of that damn beast
that's not even human!

58
00:03:43,637 --> 00:03:47,057
We were hiding like rats,
cowering in fear!

59
00:03:47,725 --> 00:03:50,477
Am I the only one who feels like shit?

60
00:03:51,395 --> 00:03:53,188
You all do, don't you?

61
00:03:53,272 --> 00:03:55,315
Didn't I tell you before?

62
00:03:55,399 --> 00:03:57,943
A hunter doesn't hunt
because of a personal grudge.

63
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:01,572
Damn you.

64
00:04:06,493 --> 00:04:07,661
Wait a second.

65
00:04:14,126 --> 00:04:16,128
Then who erased your memory?

66
00:04:26,889 --> 00:04:31,185
She's an ordinary human now.
How could she have erased your memories?

67
00:04:34,229 --> 00:04:37,065
What trick are you trying to pull?

68
00:04:39,193 --> 00:04:40,819
She's not the one

69
00:04:41,695 --> 00:04:43,322
who did it.

70
00:04:44,615 --> 00:04:45,741
Then who was it?

71
00:04:46,533 --> 00:04:49,745
I don't know if she was
a nine-tailed fox or what,

72
00:04:50,454 --> 00:04:52,372
but there was someone else there.

73
00:05:13,852 --> 00:05:15,521
<i>Let's date. For real.</i>

74
00:05:17,439 --> 00:05:18,565
<i>I'm serious.</i>

75
00:05:34,998 --> 00:05:36,500
This is driving me nuts.

76
00:05:37,668 --> 00:05:40,754
What's wrong with me?
I couldn't sleep at all.

77
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:46,260
And why am I so thirsty?

78
00:05:47,344 --> 00:05:48,929
Gosh.

79
00:05:49,012 --> 00:05:52,099
I'm dying of thirst,
but it's too awkward to go out.

80
00:06:00,858 --> 00:06:03,277
What was I thinking yesterday?

81
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,821
<i>Unlike you, I'm not good
at doing things half-heartedly.</i>

82
00:06:05,904 --> 00:06:08,866
<i>If I decide to do something,
I have to put all my heart into it.</i>

83
00:06:08,949 --> 00:06:10,826
Put all my heart into what?

84
00:06:10,909 --> 00:06:13,495
Then you shouldn't have led me on.

85
00:06:13,579 --> 00:06:15,080
I'm just getting started.

86
00:06:15,163 --> 00:06:18,208
What's wrong with me?

87
00:06:21,587 --> 00:06:23,338
I must've lost it.

88
00:06:33,223 --> 00:06:35,100
She's going to wake up soon.

89
00:06:36,101 --> 00:06:38,937
It's going to be so awkward.
How am I supposed to face her?

90
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,710
Did he really leave?

91
00:07:16,516 --> 00:07:18,477
This is so awkward.

92
00:07:19,770 --> 00:07:21,897
He could've just played along.

93
00:07:21,980 --> 00:07:24,107
Why did he suddenly get so bold?

94
00:07:24,191 --> 00:07:25,943
I didn't expect him to just…

95
00:07:26,443 --> 00:07:28,111
It caught me off guard.

96
00:07:33,367 --> 00:07:34,785
Oh, crap.

97
00:07:48,173 --> 00:07:49,841
Uh…

98
00:07:50,759 --> 00:07:53,428
Hi, did you sleep well?

99
00:07:53,512 --> 00:07:55,305
Yeah.

100
00:07:56,223 --> 00:07:58,016
What are you doing?

101
00:07:58,684 --> 00:08:00,644
Oh, this…

102
00:08:06,733 --> 00:08:08,276
Nothing.

103
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:11,029
I was just picking something up.

104
00:08:12,239 --> 00:08:13,490
I see.

105
00:08:18,286 --> 00:08:21,123
Leave or just stay. Make up your mind.

106
00:08:21,206 --> 00:08:24,042
Why do you keep going back and forth?
It's confusing.

107
00:08:24,584 --> 00:08:26,420
Oh, I forgot to give you this.

108
00:08:37,431 --> 00:08:38,890
I'm heading out to exercise.

109
00:08:40,058 --> 00:08:44,187
I might be late, and you could get hungry.

110
00:08:44,730 --> 00:08:47,983
You should use this
to buy yourself something to eat.

111
00:08:48,608 --> 00:08:49,776
Okay.

112
00:08:54,781 --> 00:08:57,576
But why are you suddenly
exercising at the crack of dawn?

113
00:08:57,659 --> 00:08:58,994
Well,

114
00:08:59,077 --> 00:09:00,704
I recently realized

115
00:09:01,288 --> 00:09:04,708
that my body's a total wreck right now.

116
00:09:05,709 --> 00:09:10,714
My balance is off,
and I don't have any stamina.

117
00:09:10,797 --> 00:09:11,798
I see.

118
00:09:17,763 --> 00:09:19,639
Okay, well…

119
00:09:20,974 --> 00:09:22,559
I'm off to work out.

120
00:09:24,603 --> 00:09:26,313
Oh, sure.

121
00:09:26,855 --> 00:09:28,982
- Okay.
- Yeah.

122
00:09:45,957 --> 00:09:47,000
Do you…

123
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,087
want to come along?

124
00:09:51,254 --> 00:09:52,506
What?

125
00:10:01,264 --> 00:10:02,349
<i>Si-yeol.</i>

126
00:10:02,432 --> 00:10:04,893
<i>The thing is…</i>

127
00:10:08,021 --> 00:10:09,314
<i>my memory came back.</i>

128
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:14,111
What are you people planning to do?

129
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:18,532
You don't have to worry about your friend.

130
00:10:18,615 --> 00:10:22,244
I'm only interested in the fox bead.

131
00:10:23,161 --> 00:10:26,665
<i>It's not like Si-yeol</i>
<i>will be in any real danger.</i>

132
00:10:26,748 --> 00:10:28,375
<i>I should just stay out of this.</i>

133
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:31,461
<i>Then whatever happens isn't my fault.</i>

134
00:10:37,843 --> 00:10:40,554
<i>But what if they actually kill
that nine-tailed fox?</i>

135
00:10:44,349 --> 00:10:48,270
<i>Would Si-yeol
have to live my life forever?</i>

136
00:10:48,812 --> 00:10:49,771
Gosh.

137
00:10:52,899 --> 00:10:54,568
Woo-seok.

138
00:10:54,651 --> 00:10:56,611
Oh. Dad.

139
00:10:57,988 --> 00:10:59,239
You feeling okay?

140
00:10:59,322 --> 00:11:01,825
It's not like I drank last night,

141
00:11:02,325 --> 00:11:03,785
but I don't remember a thing.

142
00:11:04,953 --> 00:11:06,496
Are you sure you're okay?

143
00:11:06,580 --> 00:11:07,747
Don't even ask.

144
00:11:07,831 --> 00:11:10,584
Maybe it was all the stress
from getting the press to bury the story

145
00:11:10,667 --> 00:11:12,794
of you beating someone up last week.

146
00:11:12,878 --> 00:11:14,880
Man, I totally blacked out.

147
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:18,425
Is it morning already?

148
00:11:18,508 --> 00:11:20,969
Today's the call-up
for the international match!

149
00:11:22,345 --> 00:11:24,681
- International match?
- Man, what time is it?

150
00:11:25,307 --> 00:11:26,558
We've got to get ready fast.

151
00:11:26,641 --> 00:11:28,602
Go wash up. I'll pack your bags.

152
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:04,971
Let's start with some stretching.

153
00:12:05,639 --> 00:12:07,933
- Stretching?
- Like this.

154
00:12:09,768 --> 00:12:11,645
Keep your feet straight.

155
00:12:11,728 --> 00:12:12,896
- Okay.
- Good job.

156
00:12:12,979 --> 00:12:15,482
- Now go down. Reach.
- Okay.

157
00:12:18,818 --> 00:12:21,071
Wait, is that it?

158
00:12:21,154 --> 00:12:22,239
Yeah.

159
00:12:22,948 --> 00:12:24,741
What? Surely not.

160
00:12:24,824 --> 00:12:27,327
Let's try again. There's no way
a human body can be that stiff.

161
00:12:27,410 --> 00:12:28,995
- What?
- Hm.

162
00:12:29,079 --> 00:12:30,872
Now, breathe out.

163
00:12:36,503 --> 00:12:38,880
- I can't go any lower.
- That's really it?

164
00:12:40,632 --> 00:12:42,259
- Something's wrong with you.
- What?

165
00:12:42,342 --> 00:12:44,219
Okay, breathe out.

166
00:12:44,302 --> 00:12:46,346
Exhale.

167
00:12:46,429 --> 00:12:47,847
See? You can go lower.

168
00:12:47,931 --> 00:12:50,058
One, two, three, four.

169
00:12:50,141 --> 00:12:51,768
Breathe out.

170
00:12:51,851 --> 00:12:53,812
- Exhale.
- I am!

171
00:12:53,895 --> 00:12:56,606
Now, the sides. The other side.

172
00:12:56,690 --> 00:12:58,775
Exhale.

173
00:12:58,858 --> 00:13:00,193
Let go, Si-yeol.

174
00:13:00,277 --> 00:13:02,279
- Let go!
- You're fine.

175
00:13:02,362 --> 00:13:04,197
I'm telling you, I'm not!

176
00:13:04,281 --> 00:13:07,284
- Stretch!
- I'm going to kill you!

177
00:13:07,367 --> 00:13:09,286
Good job.

178
00:13:10,745 --> 00:13:12,289
- Done resting?
- What?

179
00:13:13,164 --> 00:13:14,708
- Now, exhale.
- Exhale.

180
00:13:14,791 --> 00:13:17,335
- Exhale.
- Exhale!

181
00:13:19,212 --> 00:13:22,757
Si-yeol, I think I'm done.

182
00:13:22,841 --> 00:13:25,302
- What?
- I'm done exercising for today.

183
00:13:26,177 --> 00:13:29,431
What are you talking about?
We only just finished stretching.

184
00:13:31,224 --> 00:13:32,309
Let's run a bit.

185
00:13:32,392 --> 00:13:33,727
No. You go.

186
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:35,895
I'm going to rest here for a bit.

187
00:13:35,979 --> 00:13:37,605
Running just makes you sweaty.

188
00:13:39,232 --> 00:13:41,526
That's exactly why you run.

189
00:13:44,112 --> 00:13:46,781
Look at them running.
Don't they look cool?

190
00:13:47,824 --> 00:13:49,451
Running will make you feel great.

191
00:13:51,911 --> 00:13:55,373
Okay, one, two, one, two, one.

192
00:13:56,499 --> 00:13:59,502
Si-yeol,
how far do we have to run?

193
00:13:59,586 --> 00:14:03,631
Let's run just up to there.
Come on, you can do it!

194
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:07,677
You got this. Let's go!

195
00:14:08,178 --> 00:14:09,512
That's it.

196
00:14:14,768 --> 00:14:16,895
Why on earth do humans do this

197
00:14:16,978 --> 00:14:19,022
instead of using perfectly good cars?

198
00:14:20,815 --> 00:14:22,692
Isn't this self-torture?

199
00:14:27,572 --> 00:14:28,740
Here.

200
00:14:34,579 --> 00:14:36,206
The water tastes so good, right?

201
00:14:36,706 --> 00:14:38,625
Yeah, I feel much better.

202
00:14:38,708 --> 00:14:39,667
And the breeze is cool.

203
00:14:39,751 --> 00:14:40,752
Doesn't it feel good?

204
00:14:46,466 --> 00:14:48,093
I guess.

205
00:14:48,593 --> 00:14:50,095
You did great.

206
00:14:51,012 --> 00:14:53,431
I thought you'd quit halfway,
but you stuck with it.

207
00:14:54,224 --> 00:14:55,433
This is nothing.

208
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:00,897
Man, it's hot.

209
00:15:00,980 --> 00:15:04,150
You'll catch a cold
if you take that off now.

210
00:15:32,429 --> 00:15:33,555
There.

211
00:15:37,058 --> 00:15:40,103
We're already warmed up.
Do you want to do a bit more?

212
00:15:41,104 --> 00:15:42,355
What?

213
00:15:45,024 --> 00:15:47,026
Wait. Run more?

214
00:15:47,110 --> 00:15:48,945
No.

215
00:15:50,238 --> 00:15:52,031
Let's go play some soccer.

216
00:15:54,534 --> 00:15:56,744
- Do you want to make a bet?
- A bet?

217
00:15:57,287 --> 00:16:00,415
If you can take this ball from me,
I'll grant you a wish.

218
00:16:00,498 --> 00:16:02,542
- For real?
- Of course.

219
00:16:03,460 --> 00:16:06,087
How hard could it be
to take the ball from you?

220
00:16:06,171 --> 00:16:09,215
Anything I want, right? No take-backs.

221
00:16:10,425 --> 00:16:11,676
Are you even trying?

222
00:16:12,844 --> 00:16:13,761
Just you wait.

223
00:16:17,015 --> 00:16:18,475
Whoa, easy with the hands.

224
00:16:23,605 --> 00:16:24,731
Hey.

225
00:16:26,357 --> 00:16:27,650
Wait.

226
00:16:35,325 --> 00:16:37,744
Ah!

227
00:16:40,914 --> 00:16:42,916
Hey, that's a foul!

228
00:16:42,999 --> 00:16:44,876
How is that a foul?

229
00:16:45,752 --> 00:16:47,003
Here.

230
00:16:48,171 --> 00:16:50,423
Ok-sun, try harder.
Are you giving up already?

231
00:16:51,049 --> 00:16:52,884
You're wearing knee pads, right?

232
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:54,594
What?

233
00:16:56,387 --> 00:16:58,348
- Yes!
- Hey, that's a foul.

234
00:16:58,431 --> 00:17:00,767
That was really a foul.

235
00:17:20,245 --> 00:17:22,664
- I won, right?
- What?

236
00:17:23,873 --> 00:17:26,584
Why are you staring at me?
Is there something on my face?

237
00:17:27,418 --> 00:17:29,337
No, it's nothing.

238
00:17:33,466 --> 00:17:36,177
Want to go again?
It's fun now that I took it from you.

239
00:17:36,261 --> 00:17:39,097
Let's do it. No fouls this time.

240
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:40,306
You too.

241
00:17:41,808 --> 00:17:45,687
Hey, wait. I said no fouls.

242
00:17:50,608 --> 00:17:52,193
What should I wish for?

243
00:17:52,277 --> 00:17:55,530
I've only ever granted wishes.
I've never made one myself,

244
00:17:55,613 --> 00:17:57,282
so I don't know what to ask for.

245
00:17:57,365 --> 00:17:59,409
Hey, I told you that was a foul.

246
00:17:59,492 --> 00:18:02,287
Says who?
You didn't say that at the start.

247
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:05,540
Do I really have to explain
that kicking someone's shins is a foul?

248
00:18:05,623 --> 00:18:07,875
Don't be petty. Just admit I won.

249
00:18:07,959 --> 00:18:11,337
You're a pro. Do you really have to try
that hard to beat a regular person?

250
00:18:13,006 --> 00:18:15,550
Jeez, you always have a comeback.

251
00:18:16,676 --> 00:18:18,720
Fine, let's just say you won.

252
00:18:19,262 --> 00:18:20,388
Yes!

253
00:18:29,355 --> 00:18:30,815
- Give me your hand.
- What?

254
00:18:32,150 --> 00:18:34,527
We're on a date right now.

255
00:18:34,611 --> 00:18:36,863
I just want to hold hands while we walk.

256
00:19:08,102 --> 00:19:12,607
So,
what should we do when we get home?

257
00:19:12,690 --> 00:19:17,403
Actually, I'm not going home.
I've got to go train right away.

258
00:19:18,196 --> 00:19:21,574
What do you mean?
We've been working out this whole time.

259
00:19:21,658 --> 00:19:25,244
That was just my own workout.
Now I have to train with the team.

260
00:19:25,328 --> 00:19:28,581
Why bother?
It won't matter once we go back.

261
00:19:28,665 --> 00:19:30,124
I have to make money.

262
00:19:30,667 --> 00:19:33,461
They said I need to win matches
to get paid a decent amount.

263
00:19:34,545 --> 00:19:37,090
Plus, we don't have much to do right now.

264
00:19:37,173 --> 00:19:41,219
Don't we have to wait until that chairman
actually hands over the building?

265
00:19:41,719 --> 00:19:44,013
Well, yeah.

266
00:19:44,764 --> 00:19:48,142
After I get my win bonus
from this weekend's match,

267
00:19:48,226 --> 00:19:50,895
I'll treat you to something nice.
Something better than pork cutlets.

268
00:19:55,024 --> 00:19:56,109
No, wait.

269
00:19:57,026 --> 00:19:59,404
Eun-ho, should we go on a trip?

270
00:20:00,279 --> 00:20:02,031
A trip? Just like that?

271
00:20:02,115 --> 00:20:06,703
Well, the match this weekend
is in Suncheon.

272
00:20:07,328 --> 00:20:09,372
I heard the reed fields are nice there.

273
00:20:09,455 --> 00:20:14,836
We could go together, look around,
and get something nice to eat.

274
00:20:14,919 --> 00:20:16,087
How about it?

275
00:20:16,713 --> 00:20:18,381
Sure, whatever.

276
00:20:19,048 --> 00:20:20,383
That's a promise.

277
00:20:21,259 --> 00:20:23,678
Then, you should go home and rest.

278
00:20:23,761 --> 00:20:25,847
You must be tired from all that exercise.

279
00:20:26,514 --> 00:20:29,350
Actually, I just remembered
I have something to do today.

280
00:20:29,851 --> 00:20:30,893
What is it?

281
00:20:30,977 --> 00:20:34,814
We need money for the trip.
I'll make some while you train.

282
00:20:34,897 --> 00:20:36,733
- You?
- I told you.

283
00:20:36,816 --> 00:20:38,943
You should just focus on soccer

284
00:20:39,026 --> 00:20:40,903
because I'll bring home tons of money.

285
00:20:47,577 --> 00:20:48,911
INTERNATIONAL SOCCER

286
00:20:55,042 --> 00:20:57,378
- Hello, sir.
- Hello!

287
00:20:57,462 --> 00:20:59,839
- Congratulations. We love you.
- Congratulations.

288
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:03,885
Mr. Hyeon,
congratulations on the transfer.

289
00:21:03,968 --> 00:21:05,970
Are you settling in okay?

290
00:21:06,053 --> 00:21:07,013
Pardon?

291
00:21:07,096 --> 00:21:09,140
I mean, since you've transferred.

292
00:21:09,223 --> 00:21:10,224
I see.

293
00:21:10,725 --> 00:21:13,561
Well, I'm still settling in.

294
00:21:14,187 --> 00:21:16,606
Why are you so nervous? It's not like you.

295
00:21:16,689 --> 00:21:17,690
Woo-seok.

296
00:21:18,649 --> 00:21:19,901
How have you been?

297
00:21:20,860 --> 00:21:23,196
- Yeah.
- Congratulations on the transfer, man.

298
00:21:23,946 --> 00:21:26,282
Why are you only filming Woo-seok?
Get me too.

299
00:21:26,365 --> 00:21:28,284
Come on, he's world-class.

300
00:21:28,367 --> 00:21:29,327
Man, that's harsh.

301
00:21:30,286 --> 00:21:32,705
Hey, why haven't you been
answering my DMs?

302
00:21:33,539 --> 00:21:35,875
You mean… I haven't been?

303
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:39,128
Look at him, acting all distant.

304
00:21:39,212 --> 00:21:41,088
This is how people change
when they make it big.

305
00:21:41,172 --> 00:21:43,049
You need to get this on camera.

306
00:21:43,132 --> 00:21:44,258
Woo-seok!

307
00:21:44,342 --> 00:21:46,010
- Hello.
- Hello.

308
00:21:46,093 --> 00:21:47,845
- Hello.
- Am I invisible to you guys?

309
00:21:47,929 --> 00:21:50,598
Woo-seok was just so blinding.
I didn't even see you.

310
00:21:50,681 --> 00:21:52,016
Good to see you.

311
00:21:52,934 --> 00:21:54,602
- How have you been?
- Good.

312
00:21:54,685 --> 00:21:56,145
Woo-seok, I'll see you later.

313
00:21:59,482 --> 00:22:01,317
We're always rooting for you.

314
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:02,401
Thanks.

315
00:22:15,248 --> 00:22:17,166
COOKING, FOOD SERVICE

316
00:22:17,542 --> 00:22:19,126
STORE MANAGEMENT, SALES

317
00:22:19,752 --> 00:22:24,549
Let's see. What should I do to make money?

318
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:29,095
Oh, this hourly pay isn't bad.

319
00:22:29,178 --> 00:22:31,264
Do you have a problem with my resume?

320
00:22:32,723 --> 00:22:33,599
Education?

321
00:22:33,683 --> 00:22:34,892
OFFICE WORK, SALES, EDUCATION

322
00:22:34,976 --> 00:22:38,271
It's Yukyeong Gongwon, the Royal College.

323
00:22:38,354 --> 00:22:41,232
It was Korea's first
modern educational institution.

324
00:22:41,315 --> 00:22:42,650
You've never heard of it?

325
00:22:44,026 --> 00:22:47,196
Not Sungkyunkwan University.
Seonggyungwan National Academy.

326
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:48,823
Seonggyungwan never handed out diplomas.

327
00:22:50,616 --> 00:22:53,202
Certifications? Look, even without them,

328
00:22:53,286 --> 00:22:55,746
there's nothing I can't do
or haven't done--

329
00:22:55,830 --> 00:22:58,207
Hello?

330
00:23:05,256 --> 00:23:09,218
Why are they so picky
about hiring just a part-timer?

331
00:23:11,971 --> 00:23:14,098
OH SEASON GROCERY STORE NOW HIRING

332
00:23:15,182 --> 00:23:16,767
"No qualifications required."

333
00:23:16,851 --> 00:23:20,229
"No experience required,
and no age limit"?

334
00:23:28,696 --> 00:23:32,033
What the heck?
Why isn't anyone here?

335
00:23:35,536 --> 00:23:36,913
Push up a little more.

336
00:23:40,499 --> 00:23:41,667
SI-YEOL

337
00:23:41,751 --> 00:23:44,253
Where are you?

338
00:23:46,422 --> 00:23:48,341
Jeez. Hello?

339
00:23:48,424 --> 00:23:50,593
- Hey, where are you guys?
<i>- Hey, Si-yeol.</i>

340
00:23:50,676 --> 00:23:52,929
Why aren't you here?
Isn't it training time?

341
00:23:53,012 --> 00:23:55,640
What are you talking about?
Training was canceled.

342
00:23:55,723 --> 00:23:57,683
<i>You didn't get the message earlier?</i>

343
00:23:58,309 --> 00:24:00,019
Tell Si-yeol to come.

344
00:24:00,102 --> 00:24:03,230
Hey, you want to join us?
We're at the internet cafe out front.

345
00:24:03,314 --> 00:24:07,234
We have a match this weekend.
Why did they cancel training?

346
00:24:07,985 --> 00:24:09,987
Never mind. Just get over here.

347
00:24:10,071 --> 00:24:11,489
<i>Let's train by ourselves.</i>

348
00:24:11,572 --> 00:24:13,783
Hello… Hello?

349
00:24:13,866 --> 00:24:15,159
<i>- Hel…</i>
- Don't you dare--

350
00:24:15,242 --> 00:24:17,148
Man, I can't hear a thing.

351
00:24:18,079 --> 00:24:20,164
Man, he's exhausting.

352
00:24:20,665 --> 00:24:23,501
- Why?
- He wants us to come and train on our own.

353
00:24:23,584 --> 00:24:26,754
Jeez, just hearing that makes me tired.

354
00:24:26,837 --> 00:24:29,090
I could go for an iced Americano.

355
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:32,510
Iced Americano? It's freezing out.

356
00:24:33,135 --> 00:24:35,346
Have this instead.

357
00:24:36,097 --> 00:24:38,516
- Oh!
- Quick, give me one.

358
00:24:50,444 --> 00:24:51,404
Mm!

359
00:24:52,363 --> 00:24:53,656
I feel awake now.

360
00:24:54,407 --> 00:24:55,616
Mm!

361
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:56,701
It's good.

362
00:25:04,667 --> 00:25:08,546
I feel like someone's been watching me
from behind for a while now.

363
00:25:08,629 --> 00:25:09,880
What?

364
00:25:13,676 --> 00:25:17,138
Don't you guys feel anything weird?

365
00:25:17,221 --> 00:25:22,059
You know, like someone's
keeping an eye on us.

366
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:24,145
Who would be looking at us?

367
00:25:24,687 --> 00:25:27,982
Come on, you're not that famous.
Don't be so full of yourself.

368
00:25:28,065 --> 00:25:30,985
- You think so?
- Beom, our base is getting wrecked!

369
00:25:31,068 --> 00:25:32,903
Oh, shoot! What the… Hey!

370
00:25:32,987 --> 00:25:34,697
- Hey.
- Man.

371
00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:36,449
I did warn you.

372
00:25:36,637 --> 00:25:39,890
OH SEASON GROCERY STORE

373
00:25:39,972 --> 00:25:41,557
STANDARD EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT
EUN-HO

374
00:25:49,104 --> 00:25:51,523
So, what's your name?

375
00:25:52,441 --> 00:25:53,734
Eun-ho.

376
00:25:54,943 --> 00:25:56,361
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
KIM OK-SUN

377
00:25:57,571 --> 00:25:58,572
EUN-HO

378
00:25:59,698 --> 00:26:00,949
It doesn't say that here.

379
00:26:04,036 --> 00:26:07,247
Ms. Kim Ok-sun,
this is an employment contract.

380
00:26:07,331 --> 00:26:09,124
You have to write your real name.

381
00:26:09,208 --> 00:26:12,419
How many times do I have to say it?
That's the fake name.

382
00:26:12,502 --> 00:26:14,463
Eun-ho is my real name.

383
00:26:18,383 --> 00:26:19,635
EUN-HO

384
00:26:20,469 --> 00:26:22,304
KIM OK-SUN

385
00:26:24,348 --> 00:26:28,060
You know, Ms. Kim Ok-sun,
you're being a little too casual.

386
00:26:29,770 --> 00:26:32,064
- What?
- Stop speaking informally to me.

387
00:26:32,564 --> 00:26:34,608
What are you good at, Ms. Ok-sun?

388
00:26:34,691 --> 00:26:36,985
You were speaking informally too just now.

389
00:26:37,069 --> 00:26:38,153
Excuse me?

390
00:26:38,946 --> 00:26:40,697
Nothing. Fine.

391
00:26:41,323 --> 00:26:43,575
It won't be easy,
but I'll take it as a unique experience.

392
00:26:43,659 --> 00:26:47,204
I'm good at everything.
There really isn't anything I can't do.

393
00:26:47,829 --> 00:26:49,998
Oh, really? We've got an ace here.

394
00:26:50,082 --> 00:26:51,583
Do you like plushies?

395
00:26:55,462 --> 00:26:57,214
Oh my. How cute.

396
00:27:02,219 --> 00:27:03,387
Oh!

397
00:27:05,973 --> 00:27:07,891
Why'd you take that? Throw it away.

398
00:27:07,975 --> 00:27:09,059
Damn it.

399
00:27:14,439 --> 00:27:15,857
Seriously?

400
00:27:21,989 --> 00:27:23,448
I don't want it.

401
00:27:25,158 --> 00:27:27,744
Hey, you!

402
00:27:28,870 --> 00:27:30,080
Ow!

403
00:27:32,124 --> 00:27:33,667
- Wow!
- What's that?

404
00:27:33,750 --> 00:27:36,920
Stay back!
Don't come here. Go away!

405
00:27:37,004 --> 00:27:39,840
Hey, stop! It'll come off!

406
00:27:50,392 --> 00:27:51,768
DAEHEUNG CITIZENS FC

407
00:27:57,149 --> 00:27:59,985
Oh gosh, sir…

408
00:28:01,445 --> 00:28:02,404
Why are you here?

409
00:28:02,487 --> 00:28:05,449
Coach, I knocked a bunch of times.

410
00:28:09,202 --> 00:28:10,120
What do you want?

411
00:28:10,203 --> 00:28:11,747
Is today's training really canceled?

412
00:28:15,208 --> 00:28:18,045
Yeah. Didn't you get the message?

413
00:28:18,128 --> 00:28:21,715
What we need is more practice,
so how could you…

414
00:28:21,798 --> 00:28:22,924
Man.

415
00:28:24,718 --> 00:28:27,012
Wait. What is that smell?

416
00:28:33,352 --> 00:28:34,811
Coach, were you drinking?

417
00:28:35,395 --> 00:28:37,606
The match is right around the corner,

418
00:28:37,689 --> 00:28:39,524
but you canceled practice, and now this?

419
00:28:39,608 --> 00:28:41,485
Gosh, I'm hungover.

420
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:44,988
Si-yeol, did you eat yet?

421
00:28:46,073 --> 00:28:47,157
Pardon?

422
00:28:47,699 --> 00:28:48,825
Let's go grab a bite.

423
00:28:50,744 --> 00:28:51,703
Gosh.

424
00:29:09,805 --> 00:29:12,599
- What is this?
- It's totally burnt.

425
00:29:13,308 --> 00:29:14,810
You expect us to eat this?

426
00:29:15,435 --> 00:29:17,938
Should I throw it away then?
That's wasteful.

427
00:29:19,272 --> 00:29:20,440
Man, I burnt another one.

428
00:29:21,316 --> 00:29:23,151
It's because you kept talking to me.

429
00:29:23,235 --> 00:29:25,529
Just eat and move along.

430
00:29:29,366 --> 00:29:30,700
I'm not buying this.

431
00:29:40,085 --> 00:29:42,170
Maybe this is a bit too burnt.

432
00:29:44,548 --> 00:29:47,008
<i>Don't cause trouble this time.</i>

433
00:29:47,092 --> 00:29:49,136
<i>Got it, Ms. Kim Ok-sun?</i>

434
00:29:49,219 --> 00:29:50,804
This is much better.

435
00:29:50,887 --> 00:29:54,474
They should've put me
on this from the start.

436
00:30:04,317 --> 00:30:06,570
Come over here! I'll ring you up.

437
00:30:34,431 --> 00:30:35,599
What?

438
00:30:40,061 --> 00:30:42,063
I don't think the discount was applied.

439
00:30:43,231 --> 00:30:45,108
- What?
- Look, right here.

440
00:30:45,192 --> 00:30:47,152
You need to ring it up again.

441
00:30:48,862 --> 00:30:49,863
Jeez.

442
00:30:54,409 --> 00:30:56,077
Hm…

443
00:30:56,161 --> 00:30:57,746
CHECK RECEIPT, CHECK PRICE

444
00:31:00,999 --> 00:31:02,459
Cancel…

445
00:31:09,174 --> 00:31:12,928
Look, I don't know how to cancel this.

446
00:31:13,011 --> 00:31:15,096
- Can't we just let it slide?
- Excuse me?

447
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:19,226
Also, I like being cashier,
so don't file a complaint.

448
00:31:19,309 --> 00:31:21,311
- Let's keep this between us.
- That's ridiculous--

449
00:31:21,394 --> 00:31:23,313
Just consider the 1,750 won as a donation.

450
00:31:25,649 --> 00:31:27,943
It'll bring you good luck.

451
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:47,587
I knew it was going too smoothly.

452
00:31:47,671 --> 00:31:49,381
Gosh, this is chaos.

453
00:31:49,881 --> 00:31:52,342
Maybe I should've just let them complain.

454
00:31:55,011 --> 00:31:56,346
Excuse me.

455
00:31:58,181 --> 00:31:59,599
A check?

456
00:32:01,142 --> 00:32:02,561
You don't have cash or a card?

457
00:32:02,644 --> 00:32:04,646
Why? Is there a problem?

458
00:32:06,565 --> 00:32:09,109
Just use a card.
I don't know how to process that.

459
00:32:09,192 --> 00:32:12,487
If you have a problem with that,
you should file a complaint.

460
00:32:12,571 --> 00:32:14,114
- Excuse me?
- A complaint.

461
00:32:14,197 --> 00:32:15,907
Ma'am, let me help you with that.

462
00:32:18,243 --> 00:32:20,870
Just press this, and then this for checks.

463
00:32:20,954 --> 00:32:23,957
Get a signature on the back
and give her the change.

464
00:32:24,708 --> 00:32:26,668
Okay. Thanks.

465
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:32,340
Sorry about that.

466
00:32:32,924 --> 00:32:34,009
Oh.

467
00:32:43,560 --> 00:32:44,978
You're not drinking, right?

468
00:32:45,812 --> 00:32:46,896
No.

469
00:32:52,652 --> 00:32:54,029
Gosh.

470
00:32:54,654 --> 00:32:57,741
Who drinks soju like it's water?

471
00:33:03,580 --> 00:33:05,081
What's going on?

472
00:33:06,499 --> 00:33:07,667
Hey, Si-yeol.

473
00:33:10,170 --> 00:33:11,171
We're done for.

474
00:33:12,422 --> 00:33:14,215
What do you mean?

475
00:33:15,091 --> 00:33:18,553
I'm talking about our team, you punk.

476
00:33:18,637 --> 00:33:21,014
Come on, Coach.

477
00:33:21,848 --> 00:33:24,392
We're last in the fourth division.
We can't get any lower.

478
00:33:24,476 --> 00:33:27,270
How can we be "done for"?

479
00:33:28,021 --> 00:33:29,814
I told you, I'll get us promoted.

480
00:33:29,898 --> 00:33:32,442
Promotion doesn't even matter.

481
00:33:34,527 --> 00:33:35,612
You know

482
00:33:36,571 --> 00:33:38,948
the director who sponsors us, right?

483
00:33:39,658 --> 00:33:41,785
The director at my grandma's nursing home?

484
00:33:42,452 --> 00:33:43,370
Yes, him.

485
00:33:43,953 --> 00:33:45,330
Well, that director said

486
00:33:46,498 --> 00:33:49,250
he can't sponsor us anymore.

487
00:33:50,752 --> 00:33:52,462
What?

488
00:33:52,545 --> 00:33:55,256
A sponsorship contract isn't a joke.

489
00:33:55,340 --> 00:33:56,758
He can't just break it overnight.

490
00:33:56,841 --> 00:34:00,804
Well, what else can we do?

491
00:34:01,596 --> 00:34:05,308
Like you said,
we're in the fourth division.

492
00:34:06,059 --> 00:34:10,980
It's not exactly good publicity
to sponsor the last-place team.

493
00:34:11,064 --> 00:34:13,525
The director
was just sponsoring us for years

494
00:34:14,067 --> 00:34:18,154
as a service to the community
because he liked soccer.

495
00:34:18,905 --> 00:34:22,325
But he said he can't afford it anymore,
so there's nothing we can do.

496
00:34:28,498 --> 00:34:29,541
Then,

497
00:34:30,834 --> 00:34:32,085
what do we do now?

498
00:34:33,795 --> 00:34:35,547
What happens to the team?

499
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:37,924
We have to find a new sponsor.

500
00:34:38,550 --> 00:34:40,051
It won't be easy, though.

501
00:34:41,302 --> 00:34:43,304
We're not going down like this.

502
00:34:43,388 --> 00:34:45,515
No, I mean

503
00:34:45,598 --> 00:34:47,726
what happens if we don't find one?

504
00:34:47,809 --> 00:34:49,477
What do you think, you punk?

505
00:34:49,561 --> 00:34:53,481
The club goes bankrupt,
and the team disbands.

506
00:35:02,782 --> 00:35:04,451
Forget about paying the players.

507
00:35:06,536 --> 00:35:09,372
We can't even pay the rent
for the training ground.

508
00:35:10,498 --> 00:35:11,916
What can we do?

509
00:35:17,881 --> 00:35:20,592
Don't tell the other guys, okay?

510
00:35:22,802 --> 00:35:24,929
I shouldn't have even told you.

511
00:35:26,514 --> 00:35:29,934
I just had to get it off my chest.

512
00:35:42,572 --> 00:35:44,324
I've been thinking.

513
00:35:45,533 --> 00:35:49,037
I don't think
you're a good fit for our store.

514
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:51,873
I'll pay you for your work today,

515
00:35:52,415 --> 00:35:54,250
but you don't need to come in anymore.

516
00:35:54,334 --> 00:35:56,127
Really? That's fine.

517
00:35:57,086 --> 00:36:00,924
The pay was too low
for the workload anyway.

518
00:36:08,139 --> 00:36:09,432
I'm sorry to bother you,

519
00:36:09,516 --> 00:36:11,726
but the totals aren't adding up.

520
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,062
What?

521
00:36:14,145 --> 00:36:16,105
Ms. Kim's cash drawer is off.

522
00:36:34,249 --> 00:36:36,501
Oh…

523
00:36:36,584 --> 00:36:37,794
What did I just do?

524
00:36:38,419 --> 00:36:42,674
You gave the customer back
her 100,000-won check and the change.

525
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:46,344
That explains
why we're exactly 100,000 won short.

526
00:36:47,053 --> 00:36:50,557
So, what happens to me?

527
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,183
It's okay.

528
00:36:52,267 --> 00:36:55,854
Mistakes happen. Don't worry about it.

529
00:36:56,521 --> 00:36:57,564
Really?

530
00:36:58,982 --> 00:37:00,358
Of course.

531
00:37:00,441 --> 00:37:02,861
Just pay it back. No big deal.

532
00:37:03,736 --> 00:37:04,863
What?

533
00:37:04,946 --> 00:37:07,740
Your hourly pay is 10,030 won,

534
00:37:07,824 --> 00:37:11,202
and you worked for five hours,
so that's 50,150 won for today.

535
00:37:11,286 --> 00:37:14,330
But with the 100,000 won loss…

536
00:37:16,207 --> 00:37:19,544
…you just owe us 49,850 won.

537
00:37:21,004 --> 00:37:22,171
Owe you?

538
00:37:22,881 --> 00:37:27,677
You mean you're not even paying me,

539
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,805
but I have to pay you 49,850 won?

540
00:37:30,889 --> 00:37:33,182
I worked like a dog
all day for this place!

541
00:37:33,850 --> 00:37:35,143
That's too bad.

542
00:37:39,147 --> 00:37:41,482
I walked here just to save bus fare!

543
00:37:42,275 --> 00:37:44,152
Can't you let this slide?

544
00:37:45,737 --> 00:37:48,573
I can't do that.
I'm just an employee here.

545
00:38:08,009 --> 00:38:11,220
I bragged about bringing home money.

546
00:38:11,304 --> 00:38:12,972
What do I tell Si-yeol?

547
00:38:13,973 --> 00:38:17,352
I can't say I worked all day
just to end up in debt.

548
00:38:21,564 --> 00:38:23,608
Should I sell the clothes?

549
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:39,165
- Si-yeol, you're home!
- Yeah.

550
00:38:40,625 --> 00:38:42,543
- What's wrong?
- What?

551
00:38:43,294 --> 00:38:46,881
I mean, you went to training,
and you're back looking so dejected again.

552
00:38:47,423 --> 00:38:49,717
Well, that's…

553
00:38:54,931 --> 00:38:57,183
It's nothing.
The team's just having some issues.

554
00:38:58,685 --> 00:39:01,145
Si-yeol, want me to cheer you up?

555
00:39:01,771 --> 00:39:03,564
All of a sudden?

556
00:39:03,648 --> 00:39:05,400
Here. I made some money.

557
00:39:08,152 --> 00:39:11,531
Wow, it's pretty thick.

558
00:39:14,158 --> 00:39:17,537
- How much is this?
- It's 200,000 won. I did good, right?

559
00:39:18,830 --> 00:39:22,000
Wait, what did you do
to get 200,000 won in a day?

560
00:39:23,459 --> 00:39:26,045
You didn't steal this, did you?

561
00:39:27,964 --> 00:39:30,049
I'm on a mission
to do good deeds right now.

562
00:39:30,133 --> 00:39:33,594
How can you say that
to someone who's trying to live right?

563
00:39:33,678 --> 00:39:35,888
I know. You're right.

564
00:39:36,389 --> 00:39:38,141
But where did you earn this much in a--

565
00:39:38,224 --> 00:39:41,102
I've got skills.
I've been around the block, you know.

566
00:39:41,811 --> 00:39:43,813
The details are a trade secret.

567
00:39:44,439 --> 00:39:47,316
You haven't eaten yet, right?
Let's go out. It's my treat.

568
00:39:52,030 --> 00:39:54,407
I told you
to fix your doorbell already.

569
00:39:54,490 --> 00:39:56,784
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

570
00:39:57,452 --> 00:39:59,454
What are you guys doing here?

571
00:40:01,122 --> 00:40:04,208
Did you guys hear something?

572
00:40:05,084 --> 00:40:06,002
Hear what?

573
00:40:06,607 --> 00:40:08,796
The international match is today.

574
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:10,131
We came to watch it together.

575
00:40:10,214 --> 00:40:11,841
Hello, Eun-ho.

576
00:40:28,900 --> 00:40:29,901
Ooh!

577
00:40:29,984 --> 00:40:30,943
Hey!

578
00:40:31,027 --> 00:40:32,278
Whoa!

579
00:40:37,408 --> 00:40:40,078
Eun-ho, you haven't tried
my family's <i>galbi,</i> right?

580
00:40:40,161 --> 00:40:42,288
Jeong-bae's folks
bought a building selling this <i>galbi.</i>

581
00:40:42,371 --> 00:40:43,456
It's good.

582
00:40:43,539 --> 00:40:45,958
Really? I haven't had beef <i>galbi</i>
in a while.

583
00:40:47,710 --> 00:40:50,963
Why couldn't you guys
just watch the game at home?

584
00:40:51,047 --> 00:40:53,049
Come on, don't be like that.

585
00:40:53,132 --> 00:40:55,802
We always watch
the international games here together.

586
00:40:56,344 --> 00:40:58,387
Aren't you glad we're here, Eun-ho?

587
00:40:59,722 --> 00:41:02,683
Of course. Beef <i>galbi </i>is always welcome.

588
00:41:03,768 --> 00:41:05,645
Let's eat.

589
00:41:05,728 --> 00:41:08,397
How can you call yourself an athlete
when you're drinking this late?

590
00:41:08,481 --> 00:41:10,817
Again with the nagging.

591
00:41:10,900 --> 00:41:13,319
You don't have to drink.

592
00:41:13,402 --> 00:41:17,365
Today's a good day,
so how about just one, okay?

593
00:41:18,116 --> 00:41:19,992
Would you like a glass, Eun-ho?

594
00:41:20,076 --> 00:41:21,786
Sure, pour me one.

595
00:41:24,872 --> 00:41:27,333
Okay, fine.

596
00:41:27,416 --> 00:41:30,294
What's the point of nagging
you guys anyway?

597
00:41:30,378 --> 00:41:31,587
Just don't overdo it.

598
00:41:32,338 --> 00:41:33,673
Okay!

599
00:41:33,756 --> 00:41:36,134
Nice seeing you again, Eun-ho.

600
00:41:36,217 --> 00:41:38,553
- Nice to see you!
- Cheers!

601
00:41:51,107 --> 00:41:53,317
You know, it's really weird.

602
00:41:54,152 --> 00:41:55,153
What is?

603
00:41:56,487 --> 00:41:58,906
Actually, since yesterday…

604
00:41:58,990 --> 00:42:01,993
Man, it's getting chilly.
I might catch a cold.

605
00:42:06,539 --> 00:42:08,624
They must've fixed the streetlight.

606
00:42:08,708 --> 00:42:10,251
It had been left broken for months.

607
00:42:16,757 --> 00:42:17,800
What the…

608
00:42:18,801 --> 00:42:19,802
Who is it?

609
00:42:31,522 --> 00:42:32,982
<i>You were stalked?</i>

610
00:42:33,482 --> 00:42:35,693
Who'd stalk you?

611
00:42:35,776 --> 00:42:38,487
I know how crazy it sounds--

612
00:42:38,571 --> 00:42:41,157
Beom, were you up all night gaming again?

613
00:42:41,240 --> 00:42:43,326
It's because you're tired, that's all.

614
00:42:43,409 --> 00:42:45,411
See? You've got dark circles
under your eyes.

615
00:42:45,494 --> 00:42:46,913
That's…

616
00:42:48,039 --> 00:42:50,041
just because I'm stressed out.

617
00:42:50,124 --> 00:42:52,168
Why are you stressed?

618
00:42:52,251 --> 00:42:53,961
Bet his stocks tanked again.

619
00:42:54,045 --> 00:42:56,964
How's that my fault?
The domestic market is a total mess.

620
00:42:57,673 --> 00:43:01,510
I thought Si-yeol was the only one broke,
but you're penniless too, aren't you?

621
00:43:01,594 --> 00:43:04,096
Come on, I'm different from Si-yeol.

622
00:43:04,180 --> 00:43:05,806
He's all about soccer without a plan,

623
00:43:05,890 --> 00:43:09,101
and I ended up like this
trying to prepare for the future.

624
00:43:10,853 --> 00:43:13,064
What is it?

625
00:43:14,899 --> 00:43:16,984
What was that just now?

626
00:43:17,068 --> 00:43:20,321
Something flashed. Was it lightning?

627
00:43:20,947 --> 00:43:22,448
But the sky is clear.

628
00:43:30,081 --> 00:43:32,124
Si-yeol.

629
00:43:32,208 --> 00:43:33,417
Come out for a second.

630
00:43:38,005 --> 00:43:40,800
What's the matter all of a sudden?

631
00:43:42,218 --> 00:43:45,137
Come out. How long are you going to hide?

632
00:43:45,221 --> 00:43:48,891
What?

633
00:43:50,601 --> 00:43:51,894
Hello, sis.

634
00:43:53,896 --> 00:43:55,189
Ah…

635
00:44:09,120 --> 00:44:11,497
- It's me, Secretary Choi.
- Come in.

636
00:44:21,507 --> 00:44:22,591
Hey.

637
00:44:22,675 --> 00:44:25,303
Congratulations on returning home, sir.

638
00:44:27,847 --> 00:44:31,851
Honestly, I've always hated this place
because my old man was here.

639
00:44:31,934 --> 00:44:33,394
It was more fun out there.

640
00:44:34,854 --> 00:44:38,983
But you know, after wandering around,

641
00:44:39,066 --> 00:44:40,443
there really is no place like home.

642
00:44:40,526 --> 00:44:43,946
After ten years,
it was even nice to see my father.

643
00:44:45,281 --> 00:44:46,741
Are you back for good now, sir?

644
00:44:50,369 --> 00:44:53,456
Of course. No need for me to run anymore.

645
00:44:54,790 --> 00:44:57,877
Anyway, what's that damn shaman up to?

646
00:45:02,590 --> 00:45:06,844
He's searching every
antique shop and bookstore in the country.

647
00:45:06,927 --> 00:45:08,721
Seems like he's looking for something.

648
00:45:10,431 --> 00:45:14,060
He told me to wait and do nothing,
but what the hell is he doing?

649
00:45:14,143 --> 00:45:16,854
I need him to catch that other fox

650
00:45:17,521 --> 00:45:20,566
so I can get on with my business,
damn it.

651
00:45:20,649 --> 00:45:23,986
Also, the fourth-division soccer matter
is proceeding as you've requested.

652
00:45:24,070 --> 00:45:26,072
Oh, really?

653
00:45:26,739 --> 00:45:28,282
How are you proceeding with it?

654
00:45:30,284 --> 00:45:32,828
I found corruption and nepotism
at the sponsoring nursing home

655
00:45:32,912 --> 00:45:34,705
tied to its founding family.

656
00:45:34,789 --> 00:45:37,416
I told them to choose
between the whole family going to jail

657
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:38,751
or ending the sponsorship.

658
00:45:39,377 --> 00:45:42,254
They should've announced
the termination of the sponsorship by now.

659
00:45:42,338 --> 00:45:43,631
Good job.

660
00:45:45,299 --> 00:45:47,510
How did you know I was here?

661
00:45:47,593 --> 00:45:50,179
That light earlier.
You gained spiritual power, didn't you?

662
00:45:51,680 --> 00:45:53,432
- Really?
- Yeah.

663
00:45:53,516 --> 00:45:55,935
Yes, I did.
I got a huge amount of spiritual power.

664
00:45:56,018 --> 00:45:59,688
A few more times like this,
and I'll have nine tails in no time.

665
00:45:59,772 --> 00:46:03,109
That old man, Chairman Kim, worked fast.

666
00:46:05,945 --> 00:46:08,697
Anyway, why were you hiding there?

667
00:46:08,781 --> 00:46:11,200
You could've just said you were here.

668
00:46:12,701 --> 00:46:13,744
Pardon?

669
00:46:14,328 --> 00:46:15,746
Was it because of the guys inside?

670
00:46:15,830 --> 00:46:17,873
Since when did she have that kind of tact?

671
00:46:17,957 --> 00:46:19,458
How long have you been there?

672
00:46:20,209 --> 00:46:22,837
Well, since the beginning?

673
00:46:25,965 --> 00:46:27,758
You're acting suspicious.

674
00:46:31,554 --> 00:46:32,555
Hold on.

675
00:46:34,056 --> 00:46:37,268
You weren't here for us, were you?

676
00:46:39,937 --> 00:46:43,482
Don't tell me you're the one
stalking that stock junkie?

677
00:46:59,623 --> 00:47:01,292
Yes.

678
00:47:01,375 --> 00:47:02,418
What?

679
00:47:07,616 --> 00:47:09,493
Man, we're out of sauce.

680
00:47:10,202 --> 00:47:12,455
Our beef <i>galbi</i> is already seasoned.

681
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:14,248
It tastes better just as it is.

682
00:47:15,124 --> 00:47:17,918
No, I like the sauce. I'll go buy some.

683
00:47:18,002 --> 00:47:20,296
Are you crazy?

684
00:47:25,217 --> 00:47:27,845
I should just eat it as is, right?

685
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:30,181
I was wondering if we did something wrong,

686
00:47:30,264 --> 00:47:31,932
but I guess
it was Si-yeol who messed up.

687
00:47:32,016 --> 00:47:33,934
It's not good to get involved
in a couple's fight.

688
00:47:34,018 --> 00:47:35,853
Maybe we should've left earlier.

689
00:47:35,936 --> 00:47:38,105
Well, it's not too late.

690
00:47:38,856 --> 00:47:41,775
You want to go past them
while they're going at each other?

691
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:43,652
I don't think that's a good idea.

692
00:47:44,445 --> 00:47:47,281
- We're totally trapped here.
- Yeah.

693
00:47:50,576 --> 00:47:52,828
Just turn on the TV.
The match is about to start anyway.

694
00:47:52,912 --> 00:47:53,913
- Okay.
- Shall we?

695
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:55,039
Yeah.

696
00:47:55,706 --> 00:47:56,790
Wait.

697
00:47:57,458 --> 00:47:59,168
Where did that go?

698
00:48:02,296 --> 00:48:03,506
"That"?

699
00:48:03,589 --> 00:48:06,175
You stupid eight-tailed fox.
Didn't I warn you about humans?

700
00:48:06,258 --> 00:48:08,552
Especially men, of all people?

701
00:48:08,636 --> 00:48:09,929
You didn't!

702
00:48:11,347 --> 00:48:12,723
- I didn't?
- No.

703
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:15,351
I don't think you said that.

704
00:48:16,227 --> 00:48:18,187
Do I have to spell it out for you?

705
00:48:18,270 --> 00:48:20,564
How would I know if you didn't say it?

706
00:48:20,648 --> 00:48:22,274
Just wait a second!

707
00:48:22,816 --> 00:48:24,401
Please!

708
00:48:26,195 --> 00:48:27,655
Just calm down.

709
00:48:27,738 --> 00:48:29,365
Why should I?

710
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:34,286
Come on, what is it?
Let's calmly talk about it.

711
00:48:34,370 --> 00:48:36,664
How does blowing up like that
help anything?

712
00:48:36,747 --> 00:48:41,001
You look exactly like her,
and you even act just like her.

713
00:48:42,294 --> 00:48:44,672
Listen to me carefully.

714
00:48:44,755 --> 00:48:46,549
I won't stop you from becoming human.

715
00:48:46,632 --> 00:48:47,883
But men?

716
00:48:47,967 --> 00:48:51,720
Do you know how many women
ruin their lives over men?

717
00:48:51,804 --> 00:48:54,932
- Especially naive girls like you.
- Hey.

718
00:48:55,015 --> 00:48:58,185
Girls like you
need to be extra careful around men.

719
00:48:58,269 --> 00:48:59,436
Then what about you?

720
00:49:00,938 --> 00:49:02,147
What?

721
00:49:02,231 --> 00:49:03,691
I saw everything.

722
00:49:03,774 --> 00:49:05,276
You held hands,

723
00:49:05,901 --> 00:49:07,236
and last night at Namsan…

724
00:49:07,319 --> 00:49:11,699
That's… different.

725
00:49:12,199 --> 00:49:13,200
How so?

726
00:49:13,284 --> 00:49:15,703
I'm going back to how I was, and this guy…

727
00:49:19,957 --> 00:49:21,333
…is decent and great at soccer,

728
00:49:21,417 --> 00:49:24,295
despite how he looks now.

729
00:49:26,755 --> 00:49:28,007
But look at you.

730
00:49:28,090 --> 00:49:31,885
You barely know that guy,
so why are you stalking him?

731
00:49:31,969 --> 00:49:33,596
What do you even see in him?

732
00:49:33,679 --> 00:49:35,014
His face.

733
00:49:35,639 --> 00:49:37,641
Come again?

734
00:49:40,394 --> 00:49:41,770
He's good-looking.

735
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:46,900
See? This is exactly why I'm worried.

736
00:49:47,610 --> 00:49:49,653
Do you think his looks
are going to pay the bills?

737
00:49:50,863 --> 00:49:54,325
Why are you so against this?

738
00:49:54,408 --> 00:49:57,911
Let her like him. She'll learn from it.

739
00:49:57,995 --> 00:50:00,497
You said he's broke, and she's clueless!

740
00:50:00,581 --> 00:50:03,959
He should at least have something
if he's going to take care of that idiot.

741
00:50:05,210 --> 00:50:07,963
Of all the men out there…

742
00:50:09,089 --> 00:50:11,258
Isn't there anyone else?

743
00:50:13,802 --> 00:50:16,513
Sorry to interrupt.

744
00:50:16,597 --> 00:50:18,849
Right. What about him?

745
00:50:18,932 --> 00:50:21,393
At least he isn't broke.

746
00:50:21,477 --> 00:50:22,686
What?

747
00:50:22,770 --> 00:50:25,731
Jeong-bae, what's up?

748
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:30,986
Well, it's just that
we think you've been robbed.

749
00:50:32,488 --> 00:50:33,572
Robbed?

750
00:50:45,751 --> 00:50:46,627
Weird.

751
00:50:48,170 --> 00:50:49,588
Do thieves these days

752
00:50:50,547 --> 00:50:52,841
steal the AC off the wall?

753
00:50:52,925 --> 00:50:56,220
Jeez, that was the only thing
in this house worth any money.

754
00:50:56,303 --> 00:50:58,555
How did they know to take that?

755
00:50:58,639 --> 00:51:01,225
Si-yeol, is there
anything else you're missing?

756
00:51:02,101 --> 00:51:04,144
I don't know. Eun-ho.

757
00:51:05,354 --> 00:51:06,730
Are you missing anything?

758
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:09,358
Just out of curiosity…

759
00:51:11,819 --> 00:51:14,196
…did that thing double as a heater?

760
00:51:15,614 --> 00:51:17,074
No, not really.

761
00:51:17,157 --> 00:51:20,035
Right? That's a relief.

762
00:51:20,911 --> 00:51:22,496
What's with that reaction?

763
00:51:27,042 --> 00:51:28,794
So, about the AC,

764
00:51:29,420 --> 00:51:30,838
- I sold it.
- What?

765
00:51:31,463 --> 00:51:33,841
We won't be here in the summer anyway.

766
00:51:33,924 --> 00:51:35,801
It's winter and it's freezing.

767
00:51:35,884 --> 00:51:38,011
So it's not like we'll need AC, right?

768
00:51:38,887 --> 00:51:40,889
That's true.

769
00:51:41,515 --> 00:51:44,768
Good job. We're broke anyway.

770
00:51:44,852 --> 00:51:47,354
- So that's where the cash came from?
- Yeah.

771
00:51:47,438 --> 00:51:49,022
Oh, I see.

772
00:51:51,608 --> 00:51:53,861
I guess you sold it.

773
00:51:53,944 --> 00:51:55,904
Well, as long as you weren't robbed.

774
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:57,698
- Yeah.
- Right.

775
00:51:57,781 --> 00:52:00,576
How much did you get for it, Eun-ho?

776
00:52:01,952 --> 00:52:05,748
- What?
- She gave me 200,000 won.

777
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:06,915
- What?
- What?

778
00:52:06,999 --> 00:52:08,709
You sold it for 200,000 won?

779
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:11,503
Why? Was it worth more?

780
00:52:11,587 --> 00:52:14,590
That was the latest model
he bought this summer.

781
00:52:15,215 --> 00:52:17,050
It's worth at least 400,000 won.

782
00:52:17,134 --> 00:52:18,677
At least 400,000?

783
00:52:18,761 --> 00:52:22,556
Wait. What about the outdoor unit?

784
00:52:23,348 --> 00:52:24,975
Did you sell that too?

785
00:52:25,058 --> 00:52:27,603
Yeah, because you don't need it
without the AC.

786
00:52:27,686 --> 00:52:29,688
They said they'd get rid of it for me,

787
00:52:29,772 --> 00:52:31,565
even though
you usually have to pay for that.

788
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:34,902
The outdoor unit alone
must be worth over 50,000 won.

789
00:52:35,569 --> 00:52:37,279
Maybe even 100,000 won.

790
00:52:38,238 --> 00:52:41,992
Did you say 100,000 won?
People sell those too?

791
00:52:43,786 --> 00:52:45,662
Did I just get scammed?

792
00:53:11,980 --> 00:53:13,065
Hey, are you okay?

793
00:53:13,816 --> 00:53:14,900
What?

794
00:53:14,983 --> 00:53:16,527
Why are you so tense?

795
00:53:16,610 --> 00:53:18,779
It's not your first time
on the national team.

796
00:53:20,531 --> 00:53:24,493
Right. Maybe it's because
I've always dreamed of this.

797
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,956
But my heartbeat feels strange.

798
00:53:32,167 --> 00:53:33,794
What are you talking about?

799
00:53:33,877 --> 00:53:36,630
Don't be nervous. We got this.

800
00:53:39,341 --> 00:53:40,968
Jeez.

801
00:53:41,844 --> 00:53:45,430
Why is everyone drinking booze
like water in front of me today?

802
00:53:47,432 --> 00:53:50,561
If you're going to drink,
at least eat something with it. Okay?

803
00:53:51,103 --> 00:53:52,187
Here.

804
00:53:55,399 --> 00:53:59,444
Why are you so upset? These things happen.

805
00:53:59,528 --> 00:54:00,612
Si-yeol.

806
00:54:01,822 --> 00:54:04,241
Living as a human is just too hard.

807
00:54:04,867 --> 00:54:05,742
What?

808
00:54:13,625 --> 00:54:17,254
Are you crying? You should stop drinking.

809
00:54:18,088 --> 00:54:20,340
I was just trying to do things right.

810
00:54:20,424 --> 00:54:23,844
That's why I took the job at the store.

811
00:54:24,428 --> 00:54:28,849
But they worked me all day,
called me useless, and didn't pay me.

812
00:54:28,932 --> 00:54:33,186
Then they told me to pay back 49,850 won.

813
00:54:34,021 --> 00:54:36,398
What? Which store was that?

814
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:37,816
Are they insane?

815
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:42,654
So I tried to fix it
by selling used stuff online,

816
00:54:43,572 --> 00:54:46,241
but I got scammed doing that too.

817
00:54:46,742 --> 00:54:49,661
I really can't live like this anymore.

818
00:54:49,745 --> 00:54:51,872
Come on, Eun-ho.

819
00:54:52,706 --> 00:54:55,792
Eun-ho, it's okay.

820
00:54:58,045 --> 00:54:59,171
It's okay.

821
00:54:59,254 --> 00:55:02,633
You don't have to be here with me.
Go inside and watch the game.

822
00:55:03,592 --> 00:55:06,720
The international match starts soon,
doesn't it?

823
00:55:08,513 --> 00:55:10,098
What's the point of me watching that?

824
00:55:10,182 --> 00:55:15,145
I know Woo-seok is playing instead of me,

825
00:55:15,228 --> 00:55:18,857
but I don't exactly want
to watch it myself.

826
00:55:19,858 --> 00:55:23,862
It's hard for you too, right?
I'm sorry.

827
00:55:23,946 --> 00:55:27,157
Eun-ho, I didn't say that to make you cry.

828
00:55:27,908 --> 00:55:28,909
Don't worry.

829
00:55:30,035 --> 00:55:35,123
I promise I'll get you back
to your old life, okay?

830
00:55:38,043 --> 00:55:39,544
I really promise.

831
00:55:43,966 --> 00:55:45,425
What?

832
00:55:47,094 --> 00:55:48,887
We're doing just fine.

833
00:55:49,805 --> 00:55:51,431
Let's not worry too much.

834
00:56:18,208 --> 00:56:20,877
Si-yeol!

835
00:56:20,961 --> 00:56:22,546
Something big happened!

836
00:56:22,629 --> 00:56:23,922
What happened?

837
00:56:24,006 --> 00:56:26,383
Hey, Si-yeol!

838
00:56:29,177 --> 00:56:30,178
Hyeon Woo-seok collapsed!

839
00:56:31,096 --> 00:56:31,972
What?

840
00:56:39,229 --> 00:56:41,189
<i>He collapsed</i>
<i>right before the match.</i>

841
00:56:56,121 --> 00:56:57,205
- Woo-seok!
- Hey, Woo-seok!

842
00:56:57,289 --> 00:56:59,374
- Woo-seok!
- Coach!

843
00:56:59,458 --> 00:57:01,626
<i>Apparently, it was cardiac arrest.</i>

844
00:57:02,502 --> 00:57:04,838
They say he might die.

845
00:57:07,549 --> 00:57:08,550
What did you say?

846
00:57:14,598 --> 00:57:16,558
Woo-seok!

847
00:57:16,641 --> 00:57:18,477
Hey, wake up. Come on!

848
00:57:18,560 --> 00:57:20,312
Damn it!

849
00:57:25,442 --> 00:57:27,277
Over here!

850
00:57:36,453 --> 00:57:39,748
Eun-ho, what's happening right now?

851
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:43,168
- Why is Woo-seok…
- I don't know.

852
00:57:43,668 --> 00:57:45,754
I just switched your fates. That's all.

853
00:57:46,379 --> 00:57:47,714
I'm not sure what's happening.

854
00:57:47,798 --> 00:57:50,133
Wait.

855
00:57:51,051 --> 00:57:54,888
Then, what just happened to Woo-seok…

856
00:57:56,598 --> 00:57:59,184
…was the fate that was meant for me?

857
00:58:02,687 --> 00:58:05,732
Am I the reason he ended up like this?

858
00:58:07,818 --> 00:58:11,988
Woo-seok might die instead of me?

859
00:58:17,577 --> 00:58:21,540
If that's true, what happens now?

860
00:58:23,375 --> 00:58:27,796
If you go back to normal,
can we reverse all this?

861
00:58:30,132 --> 00:58:31,216
I can't reverse it.

862
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:34,302
What?

863
00:58:34,386 --> 00:58:36,638
Charging 150 joules.

864
00:58:36,721 --> 00:58:38,682
One, two, clear!

865
00:58:39,266 --> 00:58:41,810
Charging 200 joules. One, two, clear!

866
00:58:43,228 --> 00:58:44,938
<i>I can't reverse it.</i>

867
00:58:45,564 --> 00:58:48,108
If your friend dies in your place,

868
00:58:48,191 --> 00:58:51,403
there's nothing I can do,
even if I'm back to normal.

869
00:58:52,028 --> 00:58:54,447
There's no way for me to reverse your fate

870
00:58:54,531 --> 00:58:56,908
or to bring your friend back.

871
00:59:15,302 --> 00:59:17,220
SPECIAL APPEARANCE BY HONG SU-HYEON

872
00:59:42,913 --> 00:59:44,706
NO TAIL TO TELL

873
00:59:44,789 --> 00:59:49,294
{\an8}<i>Did you think tampering</i>
<i>with human fate was a trivial matter?</i>

874
00:59:49,377 --> 00:59:50,962
{\an8}Let's switch back now.

875
00:59:51,046 --> 00:59:53,048
{\an8}It's not possible right now.

876
00:59:53,131 --> 00:59:55,300
{\an8}<i>Why isn't it possible now?</i>

877
00:59:55,383 --> 00:59:58,136
{\an8}You know it too, don't you?
That you're going to die soon.

878
00:59:58,220 --> 01:00:00,847
{\an8}<i>I wouldn't sell this</i>
<i>for all the gold in the world.</i>

879
01:00:00,931 --> 01:00:03,141
{\an8}- Who are you?
<i>- I didn't expect to find</i>

880
01:00:03,225 --> 01:00:05,560
{\an8}another one hiding in a place like this.</i>

881
01:00:05,644 --> 01:00:09,231
{\an8}Fix this twisted fate
with your own two hands.

882
01:00:09,314 --> 01:00:12,025
{\an8}You want me to just die
instead of Si-yeol?

883
01:00:12,108 --> 01:00:14,277
So I need you to help me.

884
01:00:16,644 --> 01:00:18,657
{\an8}Subtitle translation by Susanna Kim

